        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A join with a sharp (angled) corner. Core Graphics draws the outer sides of the lines beyond the endpoint of the path, until they meet. If the length of the miter divided by the line width is greater than the miter limit, a bevel join is used instead. This is the default. To set the miter limit, see "
